{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a3c62b7530c34b47", "type": "tool_result", "content": "Paper 2607.04140 not found\n===CosyVoice3===\n# CosyVoice 3: Towards In-the-wild Speech Generation via Scaling-up and Post-training\narXiv: 2505.17589\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Changfeng Gao, Yuxuan Wang, Fan Yu, Tianyu Zhao, Hao Wang, Xiang Lv, Hui Wang, Chongjia Ni, Xian Shi, Keyu An, Guanrou Yang, Yabin Li, Yanni Chen, Zhifu Gao, Qian Chen, Yue Gu, Mengzhe Chen, Yafeng Chen, Shiliang Zhang, Wen Wang, Jieping Ye\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose a novel speech tokenizer derived from a large audio understanding model via supervised multi-task training to better capture paralinguistic information.\n  2. We introduce a differentiable reward optimization (DiffRO) method for post-training that directly optimizes speech tokens using back-propagation.\n  3. We validate dataset size scaling by expanding training data from ten thousand to one million hours, covering 9 languages and 18 Chinese dialects.\n  4. We demonstrate model size scaling by increasing parameters from 0.5 billion to 1.5 billion, which enhances prosody naturalness and performance on difficult tasks.\n  5. We release the CV3-Eval benchmark for zero-shot speech synthesis in the wild, featuring authentic in-the-wild data across diverse languages, domains, and emotions.\n\nTags: TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/控制-指令合成, TTS/功能-RL优化, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-方言小语种, TTS/功能-多说话人, 压缩/监督-有监督, 压缩/语义声学-混合", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "ba8965fa-9138-4b62-99b6-e4db9a6cd790", "uuid": "19e36dd1-8ead-4edc-9d2d-e6caafa673e5", "timestamp": "2026-07-07T06:53:51.807Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "Paper 2607.04140 not found\n===CosyVoice3===\n# CosyVoice 3: Towards In-the-wild Speech Generation via Scaling-up and Post-training\narXiv: 2505.17589\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Changfeng Gao, Yuxuan Wang, Fan Yu, Tianyu Zhao, Hao Wang, Xiang Lv, Hui Wang, Chongjia Ni, Xian Shi, Keyu An, Guanrou Yang, Yabin Li, Yanni Chen, Zhifu Gao, Qian Chen, Yue Gu, Mengzhe Chen, Yafeng Chen, Shiliang Zhang, Wen Wang, Jieping Ye\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose a novel speech tokenizer derived from a large audio understanding model via supervised multi-task training to better capture paralinguistic information.\n  2. We introduce a differentiable reward optimization (DiffRO) method for post-training that directly optimizes speech tokens using back-propagation.\n  3. We validate dataset size scaling by expanding training data from ten thousand to one million hours, covering 9 languages and 18 Chinese dialects.\n  4. We demonstrate model size scaling by increasing parameters from 0.5 billion to 1.5 billion, which enhances prosody naturalness and performance on difficult tasks.\n  5. We release the CV3-Eval benchmark for zero-shot speech synthesis in the wild, featuring authentic in-the-wild data across diverse languages, domains, and emotions.\n\nTags: TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/控制-指令合成, TTS/功能-RL优化, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-方言小语种, TTS/功能-多说话人, 压缩/监督-有监督, 压缩/语义声学-混合", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
