{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-bcbbf179bc9b52b5", "type": "tool_result", "content": "=== 2410.17891 ===\nPaper 2410.17891 not found\n\n=== 2502.09992 ===\nPaper 2502.09992 not found\n\n=== 2503.09573 ===\nPaper 2503.09573 not found\n\n=== 2509.26328 ===\nPaper 2509.26328 not found\n\n=== 2508.15487 ===\nPaper 2508.15487 not found\n\n=== 2409.00750 ===\n# MaskGCT: Zero-Shot Text-to-Speech with Masked Generative Codec Transformer\narXiv: 2409.00750\nAuthors: Yuancheng Wang, Haoyue Zhan, Liwei Liu, Ruihong Zeng, Haotian Guo, Jiachen Zheng, Qiang Zhang, Xueyao Zhang, Shunsi Zhang, Zhizheng Wu\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Proposes MaskGCT, a fully non-autogressive text-to-speech system that eliminates the need for explicit text-speech alignment supervision and phone-level duration prediction.\n  2. Introduces a two-stage masked generative transformer framework consisting of a text-to-semantic model and a semantic-to-acoustic model.\n  3. Trains a VQ-VAE on speech self-supervised learning representations to extract discrete semantic tokens, minimizing information loss compared to traditional k-means quantization.\n  4. Achieves human-level or state-of-the-art performance in zero-shot TTS regarding speech quality, similarity, and intelligibility on multiple benchmarks.\n  5. Demonstrates scalability to diverse speech generation tasks, including cross-lingual dubbing, emotion control, speech content editing, and voice conversion.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Transformer, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-多说话人, TTS/功能-语音编辑\n\n=== 2502.03930 ===\n# DiTAR: Diffusion Transformer Autoregressive Modeling for Speech Generation\narXiv: 2502.03930\nAuthors: Dongya Jia, Zhuo Chen, Jiawei Chen, Chenpeng Du, Jian Wu, Jian Cong, Xiaobin Zhuang, Chumin Li, Zhen Wei, Yuping Wang, Yuxuan Wang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce DiTAR, a patch-based autoregressive framework that seamlessly blends a language model and a diffusion transformer to enhance generation efficacy and reduce computational demands.\n  2. We propose a new definition of temperature and a fast temperature-based sampling method tailored for autoregressive models with diffusion loss.\n  3. We apply DiTAR to zero-shot speech generation and achieve state-of-the-art performance with a much lower computational load.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/架构-NAR-Diffusion, TTS/功能-DiT, TTS/控制-参考语音\n\n=== 2503.01710 ===\n# Spark-TTS: An Efficient LLM-Based Text-to-Speech Model with Single-Stream Decoupled Speech Tokens\narXiv: 2503.01710\nAuthors: Xinsheng Wang, Mingqi Jiang, Ziyang Ma, Ziyu Zhang, Songxiang Liu, Linqin Li, Zheng Liang, Qixi Zheng, Rui Wang, Xiaoqin Feng, Weizhen Bian, Zhen Ye, Sitong Cheng, Ruibin Yuan, Zhixian Zhao, Xinfa Zhu, Jiahao Pan, Liumeng Xue, Pengcheng Zhu, Yunlin Chen, Zhifei Li, Xie Chen, Lei Xie, Yike Guo, Wei Xue\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present BiCodec, a unified speech tokenization that generates a hybrid token stream combining semantic and global tokens to maintain linguistic fidelity while enabling attribute control.\n  2. Spark-TTS implements a comprehensive attribute control system that seamlessly integrates both coarse-grained and fine-grained voice parameters within a text LLM-compatible architecture.\n  3. We introduce VoxBox, a rigorously curated 100,000-hour speech corpus with comprehensive attribute annotations to establish a standardized benchmark for TTS research.\n\nTags: TTS, 压缩, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, 压缩/量化-VQ, 压缩/量化-FSQ, 压缩/语义声学-语义, TTS/控制-参考语音\n\n=== 2502.04128 ===\nPaper 2502.04128 not found", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "ba8965fa-9138-4b62-99b6-e4db9a6cd790", "uuid": "48882702-8849-4a91-9d92-50cb86de2bda", "timestamp": "2026-07-07T06:54:16.125Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "=== 2410.17891 ===\nPaper 2410.17891 not found\n\n=== 2502.09992 ===\nPaper 2502.09992 not found\n\n=== 2503.09573 ===\nPaper 2503.09573 not found\n\n=== 2509.26328 ===\nPaper 2509.26328 not found\n\n=== 2508.15487 ===\nPaper 2508.15487 not found\n\n=== 2409.00750 ===\n# MaskGCT: Zero-Shot Text-to-Speech with Masked Generative Codec Transformer\narXiv: 2409.00750\nAuthors: Yuancheng Wang, Haoyue Zhan, Liwei Liu, Ruihong Zeng, Haotian Guo, Jiachen Zheng, Qiang Zhang, Xueyao Zhang, Shunsi Zhang, Zhizheng Wu\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Proposes MaskGCT, a fully non-autogressive text-to-speech system that eliminates the need for explicit text-speech alignment supervision and phone-level duration prediction.\n  2. Introduces a two-stage masked generative transformer framework consisting of a text-to-semantic model and a semantic-to-acoustic model.\n  3. Trains a VQ-VAE on speech self-supervised learning representations to extract discrete semantic tokens, minimizing information loss compared to traditional k-means quantization.\n  4. Achieves human-level or state-of-the-art performance in zero-shot TTS regarding speech quality, similarity, and intelligibility on multiple benchmarks.\n  5. Demonstrates scalability to diverse speech generation tasks, including cross-lingual dubbing, emotion control, speech content editing, and voice conversion.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Transformer, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-多说话人, TTS/功能-语音编辑\n\n=== 2502.03930 ===\n# DiTAR: Diffusion Transformer Autoregressive Modeling for Speech Generation\narXiv: 2502.03930\nAuthors: Dongya Jia, Zhuo Chen, Jiawei Chen, Chenpeng Du, Jian Wu, Jian Cong, Xiaobin Zhuang, Chumin Li, Zhen Wei, Yuping Wang, Yuxuan Wang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce DiTAR, a patch-based autoregressive framework that seamlessly blends a language model and a diffusion transformer to enhance generation efficacy and reduce computational demands.\n  2. We propose a new definition of temperature and a fast temperature-based sampling method tailored for autoregressive models with diffusion loss.\n  3. We apply DiTAR to zero-shot speech generation and achieve state-of-the-art performance with a much lower computational load.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/架构-NAR-Diffusion, TTS/功能-DiT, TTS/控制-参考语音\n\n=== 2503.01710 ===\n# Spark-TTS: An Efficient LLM-Based Text-to-Speech Model with Single-Stream Decoupled Speech Tokens\narXiv: 2503.01710\nAuthors: Xinsheng Wang, Mingqi Jiang, Ziyang Ma, Ziyu Zhang, Songxiang Liu, Linqin Li, Zheng Liang, Qixi Zheng, Rui Wang, Xiaoqin Feng, Weizhen Bian, Zhen Ye, Sitong Cheng, Ruibin Yuan, Zhixian Zhao, Xinfa Zhu, Jiahao Pan, Liumeng Xue, Pengcheng Zhu, Yunlin Chen, Zhifei Li, Xie Chen, Lei Xie, Yike Guo, Wei Xue\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present BiCodec, a unified speech tokenization that generates a hybrid token stream combining semantic and global tokens to maintain linguistic fidelity while enabling attribute control.\n  2. Spark-TTS implements a comprehensive attribute control system that seamlessly integrates both coarse-grained and fine-grained voice parameters within a text LLM-compatible architecture.\n  3. We introduce VoxBox, a rigorously curated 100,000-hour speech corpus with comprehensive attribute annotations to establish a standardized benchmark for TTS research.\n\nTags: TTS, 压缩, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, 压缩/量化-VQ, 压缩/量化-FSQ, 压缩/语义声学-语义, TTS/控制-参考语音\n\n=== 2502.04128 ===\nPaper 2502.04128 not found", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
